{"info": {"author": "Channel 42", "author_email": "", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "description": "# hue_snek\n> A python Library for the Philips Hue API\n\n<div style=\"text-align: justify\">\n\n## About\nhue_snek is a python library for the Philips Hue API, that allows for easy API integration into other projects. The goal of this library is to provide the basic functions needed to interact with the Hue API, without unecessary functions.  \n\nI will add more documentation and progress reports in the following days.\n\n## Features\n\n- connect to bridge\n- get light information (name, state, modelname, etc.)\n- set light parameters  (on/off, brightness, hue, etc.)\n- get group information (name, on/off, colormode, etc.)\n- set group parameters  (on/off, brightness, hue, etc.)\n- get scene information (name, assigned group(s), etc.)\n- set scene for group   (via scene name)\n- get bridge information (name, mac, api-version, etc.)\n\n## WIP\n- Documentation\n\n## Example\n\nBasic usage of this library:\n\n</div>\n\n```python\nfrom hue_snek import Hue, Light\n\n#setup bridge\nh = Hue('your.ip.here', 'generic-username')\n\n#to check the connection to the bridge use:\nh.checkup()                     #returns 0 if connection and username OK\n\n#to get Light information use either the Light or Hue class\n\n#Light\nLight(1, h).name                #(light id, bridge)\nLight(1, h).brightness          #properties: name, brightness, hue, saturation, state\n\n#Hue\nh.get_light(2, 'name')          #parameters: see hue api\nh.get_lights('id')              #modes: obj (default, id, name, modelid\n\nh.get_group(1, 'name')          #parameters: see hue api\nh.get_groups('name')            #modes: all (default), name, type\n\n\n#to set lights or groups use either the Light or Hue Class\n\n#Light\nLight(2, h).set('bri', '124')\n\n#Hue\nh.set_light(1, 'on', 'true')\n\nh.set_group(1, 'on', 'true')\n\n#scenes can be accessed and set like this:\n\nh.get_scenes('name')            #modes: all (default), name, group\nh.set_scene(1, 'Chill')         #(group id, scene name)\n\ninfo = h.get_bridge_info()\n\nfor param, value in info.items():\n    print(param, value)\n\n```\n## Notes\n\nThis project was inspired by ![Phue](https://github.com/studioimaginaire/phue/). Check it out :)\n\n\n", "description_content_type": "text/markdown", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "https://github.com/channel-42/hue-snek", "keywords": "", "license": "", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "hue-snek-channel42", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/hue-snek-channel42/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/hue-snek-channel42/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "https://github.com/channel-42/hue-snek"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/hue-snek-channel42/0.3/", "requires_dist": ["urllib3"], "requires_python": "", "summary": "A library for the Philips Hue API", "version": "0.3", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <h1>hue_snek</h1>\n<blockquote>\n<p>A python Library for the Philips Hue API</p>\n</blockquote>\n<div>\n<h2>About</h2>\n<p>hue_snek is a python library for the Philips Hue API, that allows for easy API integration into other projects. The goal of this library is to provide the basic functions needed to interact with the Hue API, without unecessary functions.</p>\n<p>I will add more documentation and progress reports in the following days.</p>\n<h2>Features</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>connect to bridge</li>\n<li>get light information (name, state, modelname, etc.)</li>\n<li>set light parameters  (on/off, brightness, hue, etc.)</li>\n<li>get group information (name, on/off, colormode, etc.)</li>\n<li>set group parameters  (on/off, brightness, hue, etc.)</li>\n<li>get scene information (name, assigned group(s), etc.)</li>\n<li>set scene for group   (via scene name)</li>\n<li>get bridge information (name, mac, api-version, etc.)</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>WIP</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Documentation</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Example</h2>\n<p>Basic usage of this library:</p>\n</div>\n<pre><span class=\"kn\">from</span> <span class=\"nn\">hue_snek</span> <span class=\"kn\">import</span> <span class=\"n\">Hue</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">Light</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\">#setup bridge</span>\n<span class=\"n\">h</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">Hue</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s1\">'your.ip.here'</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"s1\">'generic-username'</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\">#to check the connection to the bridge use:</span>\n<span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">checkup</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>                     <span class=\"c1\">#returns 0 if connection and username OK</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\">#to get Light information use either the Light or Hue class</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\">#Light</span>\n<span class=\"n\">Light</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">name</span>                <span class=\"c1\">#(light id, bridge)</span>\n<span class=\"n\">Light</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">brightness</span>          <span class=\"c1\">#properties: name, brightness, hue, saturation, state</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\">#Hue</span>\n<span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">get_light</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"s1\">'name'</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>          <span class=\"c1\">#parameters: see hue api</span>\n<span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">get_lights</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s1\">'id'</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>              <span class=\"c1\">#modes: obj (default, id, name, modelid</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">get_group</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"s1\">'name'</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>          <span class=\"c1\">#parameters: see hue api</span>\n<span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">get_groups</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s1\">'name'</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>            <span class=\"c1\">#modes: all (default), name, type</span>\n\n\n<span class=\"c1\">#to set lights or groups use either the Light or Hue Class</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\">#Light</span>\n<span class=\"n\">Light</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">2</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">set</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s1\">'bri'</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"s1\">'124'</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\">#Hue</span>\n<span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">set_light</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"s1\">'on'</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"s1\">'true'</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">set_group</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"s1\">'on'</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"s1\">'true'</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"c1\">#scenes can be accessed and set like this:</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">get_scenes</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"s1\">'name'</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>            <span class=\"c1\">#modes: all (default), name, group</span>\n<span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">set_scene</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"s1\">'Chill'</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>         <span class=\"c1\">#(group id, scene name)</span>\n\n<span class=\"n\">info</span> <span class=\"o\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">h</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">get_bridge_info</span><span class=\"p\">()</span>\n\n<span class=\"k\">for</span> <span class=\"n\">param</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">value</span> <span class=\"ow\">in</span> <span class=\"n\">info</span><span class=\"o\">.</span><span class=\"n\">items</span><span class=\"p\">():</span>\n    <span class=\"nb\">print</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"n\">param</span><span class=\"p\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">value</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n</pre>\n<h2>Notes</h2>\n<p>This project was inspired by <img alt=\"Phue\" src=\"https://warehouse-camo.ingress.cmh1.psfhosted.org/375cfb1d4d90dc8f52f3a8c4fc8867aaf4af27c2/68747470733a2f2f6769746875622e636f6d2f73747564696f696d6167696e616972652f706875652f\">. Check it out :)</p>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 6926637, "releases": {"0.1": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "ed7cbbdc996ed4843bddee25b70991b2", "sha256": "5a80ca202c49c5355ddeba77db276b0df48e83f649a7ce2aa0c949488c177783"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "hue_snek_channel42-0.1-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "ed7cbbdc996ed4843bddee25b70991b2", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py3", "requires_python": null, "size": 6247, "upload_time": "2020-03-29T14:45:53", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2020-03-29T14:45:53.545485Z", "url": "ht